    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#5645\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">description</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>14世纪晚期， <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">descripcioun</span>，“描绘或描述的行为”，源自古法语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">description</span>（12世纪）和直接源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">descriptionem</span>（主格 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">descriptio</span>）“表现，描述，复制”，动作名词，来自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">describere</span> “写下，抄录，复制，草图”，源自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">de</span> “向下”（见 <a href=\"/cn/word/de-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of de- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">de-</a>) + <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">scribere</span> “写”（源自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*skribh-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *skribh- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*skribh-</a> “切割”）。通过“代表类别或个体的特质”这一概念，出现了“类型，种类”（1781）的意义。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "de-<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\"></div>",
      "html": "<p>在英语中，活跃的构词成分，许多动词源自法语和拉丁语，来自拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">de</i>\"向下，从下，从，离开； 关于\"（见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of de \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/de\">de</a>），在拉丁语中也用作前缀，通常表示 \"向下，离开，远离，从中间，从下面\"，但也表示 \"到底部，完全\"，因此在许多英语单词中表示 \"完全\"（强调或完成），作为其意义。</p><p>作为拉丁语前缀，它还具有撤销或反转动词动作的功能，因此它被用作纯否定词 - \"不，相反，撤销\" - 这是它作为英语中活跃前缀的主要功能，例如 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">defrost</i>（1895）， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">defuse</i>（1943）， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">de-escalate</i>（1964）等。在某些情况下，它是 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of dis- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/dis-\">dis-</a> 的缩写形式。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "*skribh-<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\"></div>",
      "html": "<p><i class=\"foreign notranslate\">*skrībh-</i> 是古印欧语根，意为“切割，分离，筛选”； 这是根词 <a rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *sker- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/*sker-\">*sker-</a>（1）“切割”的扩展形式。</p><p>它构成或衍生以下单词： <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ascribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/ascribe\">ascribe</a>（归咎于）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ascription \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/ascription\">ascription</a>（归因）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of circumscribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/circumscribe\">circumscribe</a>（限制）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of conscript \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/conscript\">conscript</a>（征召）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of conscription \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/conscription\">conscription</a>（征召）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of describe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/describe\">describe</a>（描述）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of description \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/description\">description</a>（描述）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of festschrift \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/festschrift\">festschrift</a>（纪念文集）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of inscribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/inscribe\">inscribe</a>（刻写）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of inscription \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/inscription\">inscription</a>（铭文）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of manuscript \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/manuscript\">manuscript</a>（手稿）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of postscript \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/postscript\">postscript</a>（附言）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of prescribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/prescribe\">prescribe</a>（开处方）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of prescription \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/prescription\">prescription</a>（药方）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of proscribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/proscribe\">proscribe</a>（禁止）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sans-serif \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sans-serif\">sans-serif</a>（无衬线的）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scribble \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scribble\">scribble</a>（潦草地写）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scribe\">scribe</a>（抄写员）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of script \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/script\">script</a>（手写）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scriptorium \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scriptorium\">scriptorium</a>（手稿室）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scripture \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scripture\">scripture</a>（宗教经文）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scrivener \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scrivener\">scrivener</a>（书记员）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of serif \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/serif\">serif</a>（衬线）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of shrift \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/shrift\">shrift</a>（告解）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of shrive \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/shrive\">shrive</a>（告解）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of subscribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/subscribe\">subscribe</a>（订阅）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of superscribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/superscribe\">superscribe</a>（在上方书写）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of superscript \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/superscript\">superscript</a>（上标）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of transcribe \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/transcribe\">transcribe</a>（抄写）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scarification \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scarification\">scarification</a>（瘢痕刻画）； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of scarify \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/scarify\">scarify</a>（刻痕）。</p><p>它的假定来源及它的存在的证据包括：希腊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">skariphasthai</i> “梗概描述，素描”； 拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">scribere</i> “书写”（在木材、石材、粘土等上刻画）； 拉脱维亚语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">skripat</i> “划痕，书写”； 古诺斯语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">hrifa</i> “划痕”。</p>"
